navirus-covid-19-desormais-present-toute-region-hauts-france|title=Le coronavirus est d\u00e9sormais pr\u00e9sent dans tous les Hauts-de-France|website=20 Minutes|language=fr|access-date=2 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302172701/https://www.20minutes.fr/sante/2730587-20200302-coronavirus-covid-19-desormais-present-toute-region-hauts-france|archive-date=2 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> and in the overseas territories of [[Saint Barth\u00e9lemy]] and [[Collectivity of Saint Martin|Saint Martin]].<ref name=\":33\" />\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/France medical cases}}\n\n== Simulation statistics ==\nSimulation studies helped convince the government that taking no action would result in large numbers of civilian casualties. In such a case between 30,000 and 100,000 more [[Intensive care unit|ICU]] beds would be required in the hospitals. In France there are 5,000 ''[[:fr:Service de r\u00e9animation|r\u00e9animation]]'' beds and 7,364 ICU beds.\nThis simulation was provided by [[Neil Ferguson (epidemiologist)|Neil Ferguson]], epidemiologist at the [[Imperial College London]].<ref name=\"lemonde6033149\">[https://www.lemonde.fr/planete/article/2020/03/15/coronavirus-les-simulations-alarmantes-des-epidemiologistes-pour-la-france_6033149_3244.html Coronavirus : les simulations alarmantes des \u00e9pid\u00e9miologistes pour la France] 15 March 2020 ''Le Monde''. Retrieved 15 March 2020</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n*[[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on aviation]]\n*[[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on cinema]]\n*[[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on education]]\n*[[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on religion]]\n*[[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on politics]]\n*[[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on sports]]\n*[[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on television]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n== External links ==\n{{